cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY 

The paper discusses deep neural networks (DNN) and their ability to learn abstract representations through their hierarchical architecture. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories in computer science, including cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Given the focus on DNN and their learning processes, cs.NE and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. However, the use of biased sigmoid activation functions and the potential implications for the human brain suggest that cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.SY are also relevant sub-categories.
